# Apps Script Conventions

## Style

- ES5-compatible syntax (`var`, no arrow functions) — standard for `.gs` files
- Private helpers: suffix with `_` (e.g. `getQuizSpreadsheet_`, `ensureResponsesHeaders_`)
- Use `getQuizSpreadsheet_()` for all spreadsheet access (works in editor, menu, and web app)

## ID-based linking (do not regress)

Evaluation and review use **question ID** and **quiz ID**, not response row numbers:

| Sheet | Question ID | Quiz ID |
|---|---|---|
| Questions | F | E |
| Responses | E | F |
| Evaluations | F | G |

Key helpers:

- `normalizeSheetId_(value)`, `cellText_(value)` — safe ID/text handling (trim, strip leading `'`)
- `getQuestionAndRubricByQuestionId_(questionsSheet, questionId, quizId)` — rubric lookup for grading
- `getQuestionBankForQuiz_`, `findQuestionById_`, `resolveQuestionIdForEval_` — review screen question text
- `getIdsFromResponseRow_(responsesSheet, row)` — fallback when Evaluations F/G are empty
- `ensureQuestionIds_(questionsSheet)` — backfill missing F column on Questions
- `generateShortId_()` / `generateUniqueQuestionId_` / `generateUniqueQuizId_` — 8-char IDs

## Public API surface (web + menu)

**Teacher**

- `addQuestionAndRubric(quizName, question, rubric)` — append Questions row; reuse quiz ID by name
- `getQuizEvaluationList()` — quizzes + pending counts
- `triggerEvaluation(quizId)` — grade Pending rows; omit `quizId` to grade all (spreadsheet menu)
- `getQuizReviewList()` — quizzes + evaluated counts
- `getEvaluationsForQuiz(quizId)` — returns `questionText`, `qPrompt`, `answerText`, `rubricText`, `evaluationText`, etc.
- `updateEvaluation(row, evaluationText)` — teacher edit of column E

**Student**

- `getQuizList()`, `getQuestionsForQuiz(quizId)`, `submitQuiz(studentName, quizId, answers)`

**Routing**

- `doGet(e)` — default → student; `?teach` → teacher

## Header ensure functions

Call before read/write on existing sheets (upgrades headers without wiping data):

- `ensureQuestionsHeaders_` — through column F
- `ensureResponsesHeaders_` — through column F
- `ensureEvaluationsHeaders_` — through column G

## API key

```javascript
var key = PropertiesService.getScriptProperties().getProperty('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY');
```

Never commit API keys. Document Script Properties setup in comments near `triggerEvaluation`.

## Common pitfalls (avoid regressions)

```javascript
// ❌ setColumnWidths does NOT accept an array — use setColumnWidth per column
sheet.setColumnWidths(1, 5, [160, 160, 300, 300, 400]);

// ✅
for (var i = 0; i < widths.length; i++) {
  sheet.setColumnWidth(i + 1, widths[i]);
}

// ❌ 4-arg getRange(row, col, row, col) is (startRow, startCol, numRows, numCols)
evalSheet.getRange(2, 1, 2, 4); // selects 2 rows!

// ✅ use A1 notation
evalSheet.getRange('A2:D2').setValues([[a, b, c, d]]);
```

- When reading Questions `A2:F`, indices are: `[1]` question, `[2]` rubric, `[4]` quiz ID, `[5]` question ID
- When reading Evaluations `A2:G`, indices are: `[4]` AI feedback, `[5]` question ID, `[6]` quiz ID
- Responses **must** have headers in row 1; call `ensureResponsesHeaders_` before reading/writing
- Wrap `UrlFetchApp.fetch` + `JSON.parse` in try/catch; use `muteHttpExceptions: true`
- Menu actions that need user feedback: wrap in alert helper (see `runEvaluationWithAlert`)

## OAuth scopes (appsscript.json)

Required: `spreadsheets.currentonly`, `script.external_request`
